opencli browser ankiweb fill 17 "<b>Daily AI Reading Reinforcement</b> bridges the gap between rote memorization and practical language application. It automatically extracts the vocabulary or flashcards you've studied today and leverages AI to generate a short, engaging reading passage incorporating those exact terms.<br><br>By reading a coherent story or article constructed from your daily study material, you naturally reinforce your memory through context, shifting from isolated flashcard drilling to active reading comprehension.<br><br><b>Key Features:</b><ul><li><b>Contextual Reinforcement</b>: See your newly learned vocabulary in a natural context to dramatically improve retention.</li><li><b>Tailored to Your Progress</b>: Extracts new cards and failed review cards that you studied <i>today</i>.</li><li><b>Customizable Prompts</b>: Dictate the language, difficulty level, and formatting for the generated articles.</li><li><b>Multi-Language Support</b>: Compact UI optimized for English, Chinese, and Japanese.</li><li><b>Closed-Loop Learning</b>: Seamlessly save the AI-generated articles back into Anki as new reading cards (created as suspended by default).</li><li><b>Flexible AI Integration</b>: Works perfectly with any OpenAI-compatible API provider (OpenAI, DeepSeek, etc.).</li></ul><b>How to use:</b><ol><li>Install the add-on and restart Anki.</li><li>Go to the add-on settings to set up your API Key and Base URL.</li><li>Click on the <i>'AI Reading Reinforcement'</i> menu entry.</li><li>Select the decks you studied today, choose the specific fields to send to the AI, and click Generate!</li></ol><i>Note: This add-on requires you to bring your own OpenAI-compatible API key.</i>"
